properties.areaDesc: East Becker; East Otter Tail; West Becker
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 7:29AM CST until February 12 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Grand Forks ND
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of less than one
inch. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph, causing blowing snow
and visibilities less than half a mile. Wind chills as low as
35 below zero.

* WHERE...West Becker, East Becker and East Otter Tail Counties.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow will significantly reduce the
visibility. The hazardous conditions will impact the morning
commute. The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for North Dakota can be found at
dot.nd.gov/travel and for Minnesota at 511mn.org, or by calling
5 1 1 in either state.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
